Detailed Description

cvmx_l2c_dut_map#

L2C_DUT_MAP = L2C DUT memory map region

Description: Address of the start of the region mapped to the duplicate tag. Can be used to read and write the raw duplicate tag CAM. Writes should be used only with great care as they can easily destroy the coherency of the memory system. In any case this region is expected to only be used for debug.

This base address should be combined with PP virtual ID, L1 way and L1 set to produce the final address as follows: addr<63:13> L2C_DUT_MAP<63:13> addr<12:11> PP VID addr<10:6> L1 way addr<5:3> L1 set addr<2:0> UNUSED

Notes: (1) The tag is 37:10 from the 38-bit OCTEON physical address after hole removal. (The hole is between DR0 and DR1. Remove the hole by subtracting 256MB from 38-bit OCTEON L2/DRAM physical addresses >= 512 MB.)
